<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Leader Says Traditional Operas Should Be Videotaped </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 9 (Xinhua) -- The chairman of the National
Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference, Li Ruihuan, said here today that traditional Chinese
operas should be videotaped to preserve the country's excellent
traditional plays.
</P>
<P>
Li was speaking at a symposium on the major performances of Luo
Yusheng, a famous North China drum artist, in the People's Great
Hall.
</P>
<P>
He said that China has developed various types of operas in its
long history, but that the outstanding artistic achievements of
many famous traditional Chinese opera artists are not known to
society because of lack of access.
</P>
<P>
The videotaping of traditional operas could be an effective way
of preserving and popularizing the rare traditional Chinese operas.
</P>
<P>
A source says that videotaping of major performances of Luo
Yusheng was proposed by Li.
</P>
<P>
North China drum music is very popular in the north, and Luo,
who is 84, has devoted nearly 70 years to the drum and has had
some remarkable achievements. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
