<HEADLINE> Fairly Strong Earthquake Hits Southern Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 9 (Xinhua) -- A fairly strong earthquake
measuring 4.5 on the Richter scale today hit the southern
Philippines, according to the Philippine Institute of Volcanology
and Seismology (Phivs).
</P>
<P>
The Phivs said that the quake happened at 9:20 p.m. for
tectonic reasons. Its epicenter was detected under the sea some
240 kilometers southeast of Davao city, the third biggest city in
the country.
</P>
<P>
It is estimated that the quake will not cause any damage. The
Phivs added that there are no aftershocks being expected.
</P>
</TEXT>
