<HEADLINE> IFC Finances Tourism Sector in Egypt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 9 (Xinhua) -- The International Finance
Corporation (IFC) today announced the approval of 25 million U.S.
dollars in financing an Egyptian company for the expansion of the
El Gouna tourism development on the Red Sea coast.
</P>
<P>
El Gouna is rapidly emerging as a popular local and
international resort on the Red Sea coast. The current phase of
expansion will help El Gouna meet the growing demand for quality
tourism facilities.
</P>
<P>
IFC's financing consists of a loan of 20 million dollars for
its own account and an equity investment of 5 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
The project is estimated to cost over 100 million dollars. Part
of IFC's long-term loan will be utilized to restructure the
existing short-term debt of the Egyptian company, Orascom Project
and Touristic Development.
</P>
<P>
IFC is a member of the World Bank Group and a leading
multilateral lending institution for private sector projects in
developing countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
