<HEADLINE> Malaysian Prime Minister Concludes Visit to Bahrain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, April 9 (Xinhua) -- Prime Minister of Malaysia
Mahathir Mohamad left Manama today for Islamabad after an
official visit to Bahrain, according to reports reaching here.
</P>
<P>
During his three-day stay, Mahathir held talks with senior
Bahraini leaders on ways and means to promote bilateral relations
and expand cooperation between the two countries, particularly in
the economic, commercial, investment and tourism fields.
</P>
<P>
They also exchanged views on the latest developments in the
regional and international arenas, as well as issues of interest
to the Islamic world, developments in south east Asia and the
Pacific, and other matters of mutual concern.
</P>
<P>
The Prime Minister of Malaysia also took part during the visit
in the works of the fifth Gulf economic symposium, delivering a
speech at its inaugural session.
</P>
<P>
Mahathir arrived in Manama last Monday from Kuwait where he also
paid a three-day official visit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
