<HEADLINE> France Deplores New Violence in Palestinian Territories </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 9 (Xinhua) -- France today deplored the new
violent incidents which broke out in the Palestinian territories,
which killed three Palestinians Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
"As we have feared, the situation continues to deteriorate and
we are worried to see that the public opinions of Israel and
Palestinians are more and more skeptical about the chance of
peace," said French Foreign Ministry spokesman Jacques
Rummelhardt.
</P>
<P>
Three Palestinians were killed and 80 wounded by Israeli troops
in the West Bank Tuesday during confrontations which also wounded
five Israelis.
</P>
<P>
"It is more urgent than ever to resume the initiative and to
propose the ideas to come out of the crisis and relaunch
dialogue," said the spokesman.
</P>
<P>
He said that France "hopes strongly that our American friends
will respond favorably" to the European initiative for a joint
action to help resume the Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
"We cannot let the situation turn worse," he added.
</P>
<P>
The French Socialist Party today also expressed its "strongest
worry" over the situation in the Palestinian territories and
called for the return of the peace "dynamic" founded on the
principle of "land for peace."
</P>
<P>
"Intransigence of (Israeli Prime Minister) Netanyahu, the
multiplication of the initiatives and declarations directly
contrary to the engagements taken and to the agreements
concluded... gravely worry all those who remain attached to the
success of the peace process," said the party in a communique.
</P>
</TEXT>
