<HEADLINE> Detroit's Hill Names NBA Player of The Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 8 (Xinhua) -- Detroit Piston forward Grant
Hill, who averaged nearly a triple-double in three road games last
week, was on Tuesday named the NBA player of the Week for games
played from Monday, March 31 through Sunday, April 6.
</P>
<P>
Hill led Detroit to a 2-1 record by averaging 29.3 points, 13.7
rebounds and 9.3 assists per game, while shooting .586 from the
field.
</P>
<P>
"Everyone who said that Grant Hill was getting tired should
look again," said Detroit head coach Doug Collins."He was
phenomenal, playing hard at both ends of the floor. Great players
play their best at crunch time and Grant proved that last week."
</P>
<P>
Hill had a career-high 35 point, 18 rebounds and six assists as
Detroit defeated Dallas, 100-82, on Tuesday. He followed that
performance with 31 points, 11 rebounds and 10 assists in the
99-92 win over San Antonio on Wednesday and closed the week with
22 points, 12 rebounds and 12 assists as the Piston lost at
Atlanta, 103-89, on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Other candidates for NBA Player of the Week were Boston's
Antonie Walker, Charlotte's Glen Rice, Houston's Matt Maloney,
Miami's Tim Hardaway, Phoenix's Kevin Johnson and Washington's Rod
Strickland. 
</P>
</TEXT>
