<HEADLINE> Xinhua International News Summary at 1600 GMT on April 9 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PYONGYANG -- A 54-member nuclear experts team from the Korean
Peninsula Energy Development Organization (KEDO) arrived Wednesday
in the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) to negotiate
the building of nuclear reactors in the DPRK.
</P>
<P>
NEW DELHI -- India will keep its nuclear options open until
there is total elimination of nuclear weapons in the world, the
Defense Ministry said in an annual report on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
NEW DELHI -- India and Pakistan agreed on Wednesday to release
each other's detained fishing boats and crew as a "humanitarian"
step to promote goodwill between the two countries, an Indian
External Affairs Ministry spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
YANGON -- About 130 more members of the Kayin National Union
(KNU), the largest anti-government ethnic armed group in Myanmar,
surrendered to the government in Kayin state last month, official
sources confirmed on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
HANOI -- Seven school children were killed and 32 others
injured when a bomb left over from the Vietnam War exploded, the
Vietnam News Agency reported on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
LUSAKA -- Zambia will not allow Zaire's former Katangese rebels
to use its territory to attack Zairean government troops, Zambian
Foreign Minister Lawrence Shimba has said.
</P>
<P>
NICOSIA -- Five new Cypriot ministers, appointed after
Tuesday's first reshuffle of President Glafcos Clerides' cabinet,
were sworn in Wednesday morning.
</P>
<P>
KAMPALA -- Uganda and Kenya will hold a peace meeting in
Moroto, Uganda, on April 14-16 to settle hostilities between
tribesmen from Uganda's northern Karamoja area and Kenya's Turkana
region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
