<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-09 16:24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Egypt Denounces Hebron Shooting Incident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, April 9 (Xinhua) -- Egypt today denounced the lastest
shooting incidents in Hebron, warning that the suspension of the
peace march would be beneficial for no one but the extremist
elements inside Israel.
</P>
<P>
Osama Baz, Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak's political
advisor, urged world's awareness to the Israeli use of force to
build settlements in Jerusalem and confiscate Palestinian lands.
</P>
<P>
"We must show to the world the extent of the acts of violence
and human abuses carried out by Israel," he told reporters a day
after Israeli soldiers and Jewish settlers shot dead three
Palestinians and wounded 103 in fierce West Bank clashes, the
bloodiest since Israel launched construction on a new Jewish
settlement in Arab East Jerusalem last month.
</P>
<P>
He warned that the use of force by any party would delay the
peace march and destroy confidence between the peace negotiating
parties.
</P>
<P>
"The Palestinians want peace," Baz said, "Even Hamas (Islamic
Resistance Movement) is not against the peace process."
</P>
<P>
He quoted leaders of the militant group as approving the right
of the Palestinian National Authority (PNA) to seek a balanced
peace that serves the required limit of Palestinian interests.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Baz said there is no confirmed information up till
now about the establishment of a military alliance involving
Jordan, Turkey and Israel.
</P>
<P>
"The Jordanian brothers are quite aware of the danger that lies
in such a step, especially as the problem in the Middle East is
not over yet and nothing has been finally settled regarding the
Palestinian cause and the Lebanese and Syrian peace tracks," he
said.
</P>
<P>
"As I understand it, an alliance is a step that is taken by
those whose interests are completely harmonious," said the
Egyptian official.
</P>
<P>
Military cooperation has been going on between Israel and
Turkey, he said, adding "but Ankara has told us clearly that it
has not entered into a military alliance with Israel."
</P>
<P>
Turkey has announced that the military cooperation between the
two countries is only limited to modernizing the Turkish fleet of
Phantoms in return for offering Israel the right of using Turkish
air space for training purposes, according to Baz.
</P>
<P>
Shifted to the Arab League's recommendation to freeze
normalization steps with the Jewish state on the 107th Arab League
council meeting here on March 30, Baz said that the Arab stance
toward the building of settlements in Jerusalem is adequate for
serving the Palestinian cause and easy to be implemented.
</P>
<P>
Israeli-Palestinian peace talks have ceased and violence has
erupted since Israel launched construction for a 6,500-home new
Jewish housing project in Arab East Jerusalem last month.
</P>
<P>
Egypt is the first Arab country to sign a peace treaty with
Israel, in 1978, at a three-way summit at Camp David of the United
States. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
