brutally detained by a dozen soldiers this morning as he was
walking toward his office under the company of more than several
hundred supporters.
</P>
<P>
An advisor of General Likulia later told AFP that Tshisekedi
was immediately released and personally accompanied home by one of
the sons of President Mobutu, Commander Kongolo Mobutu.
</P>
<P>
No motivation was given for the arrest of Tshisekedi, an
opposition leader and chronic rival of Mobutu. His supporters
staged several protests in the streets and before the parliament
in the past few days.
</P>
<P>
President Mobutu Tuesday declared a state of emergency all over
the country, while the rebels have captured all the major cities
of Zaire except Kinshasa, as well as most of the mineral rich
areas of the country. 
