<HEADLINE> 50 Iranians Arrested for Bribery, Embezzlement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 9 (Xinhua) -- Fifty Iranians involved in
bribery and embezzlement within government bureaucracies and
public firms were arrested in Hamadan, 343 kilometers southwest of
Tehran, the information ministry said here today.
</P>
<P>
The ministry said that the 50 men were arrested on charges of
embezzlement of 6.5 million U.S. dollars from the government
organizations or their affiliated firms.
</P>
<P>
This is the largest number of the people ever arrested on
charges of corruption in the country. However, the ministry did
not mention when they were arrested nor their identifications and
posts.
</P>
<P>
"By forging documents, these individuals took advantage of the
opportunities provided to them by their jobs," the ministry said,
adding that their cases had already been forwarded to the courts
and the verdicts of the courts were imminent. 
</P>
