<HEADLINE> Rebels Enter Lubumbashi in S. Zaire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, April 9 (Xinhua) -- Rebels of the Alliance of
Democratic Forces for the Liberation of Congo-Zaire (ADFL) led by
Laurent Kabila marched into Lubumbashi in triumph today, a report
from Zaire's second city said.
</P>
<P>
The rebels entered from the southern suburbs in the direction
of the Zambian border but did not reach the Post Office Square --
the city center -- at 3:30 p.m. (13:30 gmt), residents contacted
by telephone said.
</P>
<P>
Firing died down after four p.m.
</P>
<P>
"It's calm, people are leaning on their balconies waiting for
the rebels to come," said one women contacted by phone at
the city center.
</P>
<P>
Rebels said they had met fierce resistance some 15 kilometers
out of town, after which they had marched in.
</P>
<P>
"We had a serious encounter at Lion's Hill, about 15 km from
here. But Once we broke the resistance there, we just moved
ahead," said one rebel of the ADFL.
</P>
<P>
One commander said he had two wounded men. There had been
heavy mortar and gunfire through the early afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Government soldiers seemed to have fled in stolen cars toward
the airport some six km northeast of the city.
</P>
<P>
People in a crowd said many government soldiers had stripped
off their uniforms and dumped them before fleeing the rebel
advance.
</P>
<P>
Electricity and the city's main cellular telephone network
are still working in Lubumbashi even after the rebels came.
</P>
</TEXT>
