<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe's Gold Output Falls </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, April 9 (Xinhua) -- Gold output in Zimbabwe fell by
more than 200 kgs during the first two months of this year amid
concern that local companies were curtailing production due to
the low price and rising input costs.
</P>
<P>
Statistics obtained today showed that in the two months to
February, output reached 3,916.01 kgs worth more than 43.8
million U.S. Dollars.
</P>
<P>
During the same period last year, gold production reached
4,124.29 kgs then valued at 45.2 million Dollars.
</P>
<P>
Total output in 1996 was 24.72 tons worth 277 million US
Dollars, compared with 24.34 tons valued at 235 million Dollars.
</P>
</TEXT>
