<HEADLINE> Lesotho Prepares for 1998 General Elections </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, April 9 (Xinhua) -- The Lesotho government will
spend about 250,000 U.S. dollars for voter education in
preparation for the next year's general elections, a high-ranking
official said in Maseru, Lesotho today.
</P>
<P>
The money would be used immediately after the establishment of
an independent electoral commission, Lesotho Minister of Law and
Constitutional Affairs Sephiri Motanyane told parliament.
</P>
