<HEADLINE> Swearing-in by UNITA MPs Praised in Angola </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, April 9 (Xinhua) -- The swearing-in of the parliament
members of the National Union for the Total Independence of
Angola (UNITA) received positive response today from Angolan
leaders present at the inauguration ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Franca Van-Dunem, the just appointed premier of the Angolan
government of national unity and reconciliation, said the
office-taking of the UNITA deputies has enable Angola to become
"integrated", not divided by "two sides".
</P>
<P>
He said he was very glad to have taken part in the ceremony,
adding that parliament will play a greater role in Angola's
reconstruction and development.
</P>
<P>
Chief of General Staff of the Angolan armed forces Joao de
Matos noted that the swearing in of the UNITA parliament deputies
is "a major event helpful to the smooth completion of the peace
process."
</P>
<P>
After taking office today, Abel Chivukuvuku, leader of the
UNITA mps, told reporters that this event of making the
parliament "complete" is of "great importance" in that it can
work vigorously from then on.
</P>
<P>
He pledged that the UNITA parliament members will work hard
to consolidate peace and achieve national reconciliation and
reconstruction.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, delegations from Portugal, Cuba and Morocco arrived
here today to participate in the inauguration ceremony of the
Angolan government of national unity and reconciliation on
Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
