<HEADLINE> Rape on Rise in Ethiopia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 9 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian police said
today the first half of this Ethiopian year, from September 11,
1996 to March 9, 1997, had seen an unprecedented increase in rape
in various parts of the country.
</P>
<P>
The police were quoted by the Ethiopian News Agency as saying
that "922 women and under-aged children in various regions and 68
others in Addis Ababa were raped over the last six months alone."
</P>
<P>
The police disclosed that the majority of the victims are aged
between 16 and 18, some from 19 to 30 and others are below the
age of 15.
</P>
<P>
The crime is committed either individually by persons often
between the age of 19 and 30 or in a group, the police noted.
</P>
<P>
During the last Ethiopian year, 1,067 women and under-aged
children throughout the country were raped, according to the
police. 
</P>
