<P>
A six-member delegation representing the workers had a
30-minute meeting with Papaioannou, outlining their stances on
increasingly unemployment problem and raising social security
demands.
</P>
<P>
The Greek government today has criticized the workers' action,
saying it "dynamites every good effort to tackle the problems of
the people."
</P>
<P>
Andreas Zazopoulos, president of the Panhellenic Federation of
Construction Workers, accused the Greek government of
"high-handedness."
</P>
