<HEADLINE> Siemens Take Over Sections of Parsons from Rolls-Royce </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, April 9 (Xinhua) -- Germany's largest electronics and
engineering company Siemens AG announced today that it has
acquired sections of Parsons Power Generation Systems Ltd., a
power plant supplier owned by Rolls-Royce.
</P>
<P>
A contract on deal, worth about 83 million German marks, or
some 49 million U.S. dollars, was signed today in London, the
company said.
</P>
<P>
By taking over the service business for turbines and generators
supplied by Parsons, Siemens will significantly expand its market
basis in power plant services, the company said.
</P>
<P>
The acquired Parsons activities will be merged with Siemens'
existing power generation activities in Britain to form a new
company under the name of Siemens Power Generation Ltd and will be
headquartered in Newcastle where Parsons now located.
</P>
<P>
"As one of the world's most experienced manufacturers of steam
turbines and generators with a large installed base of operating
power plants and a qualified staff, Parsons is a valuable
supplement in line with our business strategy," said Hans Boehm,
member of the board of the Power Generation Group of Siemens AG.
</P>
