<HEADLINE> TSE Floor Trading to Close April 23 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Canada's leading exchange in
Toronto is set to officially close its trading floor on April 23
to move to an entirely computerized system.
</P>
<P>
The Toronto Security Exchange (TSE) will move the remaining 236
stocks of the 1,452 total onto its computer system, known as the
Computer Assisted Trading System (CATS) on April 14.
</P>
<P>
A floor-closing ceremony is planned for April 23, when the
transfer will be complete, said reports today.
</P>
<P>
The TSE originally planned to close the trading floor on April
16.
</P>
<P>
It held off moving the final stocks to give it more time to
check the computer system last week, when the system was brought
to a halt by heavy trading of Bre-X stocks.
</P>
<P>
The exchange said it is now confident the CATS is ready to take
on the load of the final stocks.
</P>
<P>
The TSE's average daily trading volume so far this year is 101
million shares. 
</P>
</TEXT>
