<HEADLINE> China's Trade Minister Calls For Global Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 10 (Xinhua) -- China's Minister of the Foreign
Trade and Economic Cooperation Wu Yi said today that all
countries, whether developed or developing, should break regional
boundaries and participate in global economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
In a speech at the closing session of the Thirty-Second World
Congress of the International Chamber of Commerce, Wu said that it
is only this that can help countries from different regions make
better use of advanced scientific and technological achievements.
</P>
<P>
The minister praised the efforts of many countries in regional
economic cooperation in the form of open markets and free trade
because they have promoted the development of regional economy and
the world economy.
</P>
<P>
However, she said, the efforts have also resulted in some new
barriers, because regional groups have tried to adopt favorable
policies for member countries and to protect regional interests,
and new confrontations have appeared between member countries and
non-member countries.
</P>
<P>
The minister said that it is important that these regional
groups open up and adopt an opening regionalism. APEC is different
from traditional regional economic groups and has a characteristic
of opening regionalism, she pointed out, emphasizing that all
achievements in free trade and investment of APEC have been shared
by other non-member countries.  
</P>
