<HEADLINE> Reima Tutta Looking at China's Children's Clothing Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Finland's Reima Tutta, the
largest producer of children's clothing in northern Europe, will
begin to market its collection in China this year.
</P>
<P>
The company has 50 years of experience in the children's
clothing business and has more than 20 outlets worldwide. It
mostly produces knitwear and outdoor clothing for children,
accounting for 75 percent of its business.
</P>
<P>
Although its sales inside China have not begun, it spent 4.5
million US dollars setting up two clothing factories, in Deqing
County in east China's Zhejiang Province and Beijing. They account
for as much as 35 percent of its sales worldwide, by exporting to
America and Europe.
</P>
<P>
The Deqing factory, which is a joint venture, can produce four
million pieces of knitwear for children annually, and the Beijing
factory, which is wholly-owned by Reima Tutta, produces 300,000
pieces of outdoor wear a year.
</P>
<P>
With their growing production capacity, the factories are
expected to provide children's collection for China's market in
addition to meeting American and European market demand.
</P>
<P>
In order to increase sales in China, Reima Tutta plans to set
up 30 small shops in shopping malls in the country's 10 biggest
cities in the first year, and open boutiques in big and
medium-sized cities in the second year, bringing the number of
outlets in the country eventually to more than 50.
</P>
<P>
China's great potential in the clothing market, its abundant
but cheap raw materials and labor, and its good relations with
Finland have encouraged Reima Tutta to increase its business
here. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
