<HEADLINE> Cyprus, Bulgaria Sign Postal-Telecommunication </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Cyprus and Bulgaria signed here
today a postal-telecommunication agreement aimed at promoting
cooperation in this field.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was signed by Cypriot Minister of Communications
and Works Leontios Ierodiaconou and his Bulgarian counterpart
Antoni Slavinski, who arrived here Wednesday for an official
visit.
</P>
<P>
The agreement provides for measures to increase the volume of
postal-telecommunication transmission and improve its quality in
cooperation between the two countries. It also stipulates means
of improving the quality of radio and TV program transmission
through the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Ierodiaconou said after the signing ceremony that the
agreement indicates that the relations between the two countries
have been strengthened not only in political field, but also in
economic, and technological ones.
</P>
<P>
Slavinski also expressed the hope that the agreement "will
open the door for the future and more active cooperation between
the two countries' postal-telecommunication authorities."
