<HEADLINE> CASC, Digital to Launch Joint Venture in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 10 (Xinhua) -- China Aerospace Corporation
(CASC) and the U.S.-based Digital Equipment Corporation have
planned to build a joint venture in China to develop, manufacture
and distribute network computers.
</P>
<P>
Under the terms of a memorandum of understanding, Digital will
provide engineering and design resources for the venture while
CASC rendering manufacturing expertise, distribution capabilities,
 and application development for the market.
</P>
<P>
The total investment, to be shared equally by the two
companies, may reach 40 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
They expected to make first shipments by the end of 1997, with
plans to produce some 150,000 units by the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
Digital brings to the venture not only its industry-leading
StrongARM microprocessor, but the ability to help leverage the
output of the venture through its broad product and service
capabilities, including high-performance servers and systems
integration expertise, said Bobby Choonavala, president of Digital
 Asia Pacific.
</P>
<P>
Hailing CASC as "an ideal partner for us in China," he
said: "CASC brings to the venture a wealth of manufacturing
expertise in personal computers, electronics and communication
devices as well as established distribution channels."
</P>
<P>
CASC, which exclusively deals with satellites and other space
products in China, have joined hands with Digital since 1994 in
distributing Digital workstations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
