<HEADLINE> Top Seeds Enter 2nd Round at Asian Junior Badminton </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Top seed Xia Xuanze of China
enjoyed an easy win of 15-8, 15-4 over Thra Soe of Burma on
Thursday and enter the second round of boys singles event in the
first Asian Junior Badminton Championships.
</P>
<P>
Girls top seed Yu Hua of China defeated Emi Euda of Japan 11-7,
11-2 in the first round.
</P>
<P>
In other main matches in the boys division, fifth seed James
Chua of Malaysia routed Chan Wai of Macau 15-1, 15-2 and
Indonesian junior champion Hartawan defeated Tay Zi Yang of
Singapore 15-3, 15-2.
</P>
<P>
In the girls division, second seed Peng Jo Yu of Taiwan blanked
Kelly Watts of the Philippines 11-0, 11-0, and No. 3 seed Lee
Kyung-won of South Korea won by default against Zha Salma of
Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
In team competition, top-seeded China beat close rival
Indonesia to capture both the boys' and girls' crowns on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The championships also included teams from Singapore, Iran,
Macau, India, the Philippines, Vietnam, Pakistan, Cambodia, Nepal,
Burma, Bangladesh, Kazakstan and Syria. 
</P>
