<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets With Cuban Delegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin, in
a meeting with a delegation from the Cuban Ministry of the
Interior today, said that strengthening Sino-Cuban friendship and
cooperation is in the fundamental interest of the two peoples.
</P>
<P>
Jiang told the group, led by Abelardo Colome Ibarra, a member
of the Political Bureau of the Central Committee of the Cuban
Communist Party, vice-president of the Council of State, and
minister of the Interior of Cuba, that the Chinese government and
people are willing to make efforts to improve relations with the
Cuban government and people.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said exchanges and cooperation between the two countries
in the economy, trade, science and technology, and culture have
increased in the past few years. And the two sides have cooperated
effectively in international affairs, he added.
</P>
<P>
Colome Ibarra briefed Jiang on the Cuban people's efforts to
overcome difficulties and build their socialist country.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that China is glad to see the Cuban people's
achievements under the leadership of President Fidel Castro, and
that Cuba has explored development in line with Cuban conditions
and adopted a series of reform and opening up measures to perfect
socialism.
</P>
<P>
Cuba has maintained political stability and economic
self-reliance and has overcome difficulties resulting from an
outside blockade and natural disasters, he said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that he is also satisfied with the continued
development of cooperation between public security, national
security and police departments of the two sides, and that it is
necessary for bilateral police cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Colome Ibarra conveyed Castro's greetings to Jiang, and Jiang
asked him to convey his regards to Castro in return.
</P>
<P>
The delegation is here at the invitation of the Public Security
Ministry. Minister of Public Security Tao Siju also held talks
with Colome Ibarra.
</P>
<P>
The delegation is also scheduled to visit Shanghai and
Guangzhou.  
</P>
</TEXT>
