<HEADLINE> New Leaders of Chinese Radio And TV Society Chosen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 10 (Xinhua) -- The China Radio &AMP; Television
Society (CRTS) has selected Ai Zhisheng, former minister of radio,
film and television, as its new president, and Liu Xiliang, who is
vice-minister of radio, film and television, as vice-president in
a three-day meeting here.
</P>
<P>
Wu Lengxi was elected as honorary president of the society.
</P>
<P>
At a closing ceremony today, Liu said that China has made great
progress in radio and TV programming since the 1980s, but with
rapid technology developments, its radio and TV industry faces new
challenges.
</P>
<P>
"Under the guidance of Maxism-Leninism, Mao Zedong Thought, and
Deng Xiaoping's theory of building socialism with Chinese
characteristics, the society should contribute more to exploring
ways of developing China's radio and television and to building up
a theory for radio and television with Chinese characteristics,"
he added.
</P>
<P>
CRTS was founded in 1986 and has more than 20,000 members
now. It has played an important role in programming, improving
management, and training.
</P>
<P>
The meeting amended the society's constitution and discussed
radio and TV programming in China. CRTS also said that a
newly-published collection of Ai's articles can help readers learn
more about the development of China's radio and television
industry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
