<HEADLINE> Excavator Causes Gas Pipe Blast in Seoul </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, April 10 (Xinhua) -- An excavator working on subway
construction in western Seoul this afternoon accidentally hit a
gas pipeline which caused a big explosion, much panic and snarled
traffic for hours -- but caused no casualties
</P>
<P>
Seoul police said the excavator, working on a sewer pipe in
Mapo district, accidentally scraped a gas pipeline. It caused a
spark which ignited leaking gas leading to the blast at a business
intersection.
</P>
<P>
Witnesses said they heard a loud explosion at 1:46 p.m. (local
time) and saw a flame skyrocketing more than 30 meters. 
</P>
</TEXT>
