<HEADLINE> Albania to Strengthen Cooperation With Macedonia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Albanian Prime Minister Bashkim
Fino has promised that his government -- despite its short term --
will try to strengthen cooperation with all countries,
particularly its neighbors such as Macedonia.
</P>
<P>
Fino made the promise during an interview, carried today, by
the newspaper, New Macedonia.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister, appointed in mid-March, said economic
cooperation would be the core of its cooperation with any other
country.
</P>
<P>
He thanked Macedonia for allowing the multinational protection
force to traverse its land to reach Albania, and for providing the
troops with logistic supplies.
</P>
<P>
He said Macedonia's proposal for sending medical teams to the
multinational force reflected the country's strong desire for
peace in Albania.
</P>
<P>
The collapse of shaky investment schemes, into which thousands
of people put their life savings, sparked widespread unrest in the
Balkan country in January and protests mushroomed across the
country. They quickly erupted into armed conflict across the
country in March.
</P>
<P>
Protesters demanded repayment of their money and the opposition
party called for the resignation of President Sali Berisha.
</P>
<P>
Fino, an economist from the opposition Socialist Party, was
invited by the president to form a new government on March 12.
</P>
<P>
This government adopted effective measures to placate the
unrest, and order is being restored in the country.
</P>
<P>
The all-party interim government, transitional in nature, will
come to the end of its mandate by June. A fresh parliamentary
election will produce a new government to run the country. 
</P>
