<HEADLINE> China's Import and Export Volume to Exceed $300 Billion in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 10 (Xinhua) -- China's foreign trade volume is
expected to hit 310 billion US dollars this year, a rise of seven
percent from 1996, Vice-Premier Li Lanqing said here today.
</P>
<P>
Li was speaking at the 32nd World Congress of the International
Chamber of Commerce which ended here today.
</P>
<P>
In keeping with its principle of "ensuring steady progress,"
the Chinese government has decided to allow more domestic
producers to deal directly with overseas companies and will
encourage local traders to serve as agents for local enterprises
to maintain growth in foreign trade and a balance between imports
and exports, Li noted.
</P>
<P>
China had a 9.7 percent increase in its GDP last year, and its
import and export volume amounted to 289 billion dollars in 1996.
