<HEADLINE> Siemens Nixdorf to Market Geographical Information System in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Germany's Siemens Nixdorf
Informationssysteme AG (SNI), Europe's largest supplier of
information technology, announced here today that it will
cooperate with two Chinese companies to market its geographical
information system, SICAD, in China.
</P>
<P>
SNI will cooperate with the Legend Group, China's largest
information technology company, and the State Surveying and
Mapping Bureau's China Siwei Surveying and Mapping Corp. to help
China improve urban planning, land administration, and urban
construction administration by providing the country with SICAD.
</P>
<P>
In addition to working with Siemens Nixdorf in marketing SICAD,
the State Bureau will cooperate with the German company in
technology development and natural disaster reduction,
agricultural and land resources survey, and environment protection
projects.
</P>
<P>
The Legend Group will help Siemens Nixdorf market SICAD in
China by providing solutions to the country's public
infrastructure construction problems.
</P>
<P>
SICAD has been successfully used in north China's Tianjin and
Dalian cities and in Shanghai, helping improve urban planning,
land construction, and administrative work.
</P>
<P>
China is also using advanced systems from the US, Australia,
and Canada to upgrade its surveying and mapping technology to
integrate it with geographical information systems, global
positional systems, remote sensing, and digital communications
networks.
</P>
<P>
While maintaining self-development, China intends to increase
cooperation with foreign information technology suppliers to help
develop the country's geographical information systems
industry. 
</P>
