<HEADLINE> China-ASEAN Cooperation Seminar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Over 50 people from Malaysia, Viet
Nam, Laos, the Philippines and China have discussed economic and
trade cooperation between China and Southeast Asian countries at a
seminar which ended here today.
</P>
<P>
The two-day seminar was jointly organized by the National
Committee for Pacific Economic Cooperation and the Commercial
Committee of the Chinese Southeast Asia Society.
</P>
<P>
Materials from the seminar show that trade between China and
Southeast Asian countries has enjoyed a sustained and fast
growth. The volume of trade between China and the ASEAN went from
9.25 billion US dollars in 1990 to 13.59 billion US dollars in
1995, said a Chinese offical at the seminar.
</P>
<P>
ASEAN has also become a major investor in China. ASEAN
investors have shifted their emphasis from labor-intensive
projects to technology-intensive ones.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, some of the Chinese enterprises have opened
metal-processing, chemical, pharmaceutical, real estate and
service firms in ASEAN countries. 
</P>
