<HEADLINE> Major Minivan Maker Set To Manufacture 80,000 Vehicles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Chongqing Chang'an Automotive
Holding Co. plans to produce and sell 80,000 minivans this year,
according to the company's annual report released here today.
</P>
<P>
China's largest compact vehicle maker last year produced and
sold 72,600 vehicles, claiming 17.7 percent of the country's total.
</P>
<P>
The company last year registered a net profit of 218 million
yuan, down 11 percent from the previous year.
</P>
<P>
The board of the company attributed the profit decrease to the
auto price cuts spread among Chinese automakers last year.
</P>
<P>
To hone its long-term competitive edge, the company this year
initiated a two-year expansion project which can generate a
capacity of 150,000 Alto-brand compact cars upon completion.
</P>
<P>
Last October, the company issued 250 million B shares traded by
overseas investors on the Shenzhen bourse. Half of the shares were
offered for overseas investors at a per-share price of 2.03
yuan. The rest were purchased by three Japanese investors,
including Suzuki Motor Corporation, at the per-share price of 2.96
yuan. The stock issuance raised 585 million yuan for the company.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, about 300 million yuan has been used
for the construction of an assembly plant and company
operations. The remaining 250 million yuan has been poured in the
Alto project.
</P>
<P>
The board also suggested to divert 7.564 million yuan from its
net profit as dividends for share-holders. The per-share interest
is 0.03 yuan, said the report. 
</P>
</TEXT>
