<HEADLINE> France Takes on Belgium in Davis Cup Play-off </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Title holder France will have to
hold off Belgium to retain their place in the Davis Cup
championship's World Group for 1998.
</P>
<P>
When the draw was made on Thursday, France, who lost to
Australia in the first round of this year's competition, were
given an away tie at Belgium, who beat Denmark in last week's
Euro/Africa Group second round.
</P>
<P>
The three-day match is fixed through September 19-21 the same
weekend as the Davis Cup semi-finals. The winners will play in
next year's 16-team World Goup with the losers going into in the
Zonal Group One competition.
</P>
<P>
The other Qualifying Round match-ups feature Zimbabwe vs
Austria, Brazil vs New Zealand, India vs Chile, Germany vs Mexico,
Russia vs Romania, Canada vs Slovakia and Switzerland vs South
Korea.
</P>
<P>
France captured the trophy by beating Sweden in a gripping
final. Sweden face Italy in this year's semi-finals, which also
feature the United States against Australia. 
</P>
