<HEADLINE> Chinese President Calls for Peace of the Middle East </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
reaffirmed here today that China supports the just cause of the
Arabs, pays close attention to the situation in the Middle East
and supports the peace process in the region.
</P>
<P>
Meeting with Syrian Vice-President Abdel Halim Khaddam, Jiang
said that the Middle East peace process has achieved some progress
based on the principle of "land for peace," adding China is
delighted with any progress in the peace process.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that the Middle East peace talks will
continue and a comprehensive and just peace will be achieved as
early as possible.
</P>
<P>
Khaddam noted that the relevant UN resolutions are the basis
for the realization of peace in the Middle East, and Syria and
Israel should resume their peace talks on the basis of the
progress already achieved through negotiations.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that the human rights issue is used by some
Western countries as an excuse to impose pressure on the
developing countries. He called on the developing countries to
unite in their struggle against such practices.
</P>
<P>
Expressing satisfaction at the development of friendly
cooperation between China and Syria, Jiang said that they are both
developing countries of Asia, and friendship between the two
peoples has a long history.
</P>
<P>
Khaddam agreed that relations between the two countries are
deep and solid, and their friendship has lasted half a
century. Syria hopes to reinforce its cooperation with China, he
added.
</P>
<P>
The vice president extended his congratulations on Hong Kong's
return to China, saying he hopes that China's reunification will
be achieved as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
Khaddam extended Syrian President Hafez al-Assad's regards to
Jiang and briefed him on the current situation in the Middle
East. Jiang in return asked Khaddam to bring his kind regards to
al-Assad, and also invited al-Assad to visit China at his
convenience. 
</P>
</TEXT>
