<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-Premier Meets Foreign Railway Officials </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Premier Zou Jiahua met today
with foreign railways officials who are in Beijing for the 10th
Railway General Directors Council of the Railway Cooperation
Organization.
</P>
<P>
The Organization was established in 1956 for scientific and
technical cooperation on the Eurasia railway. A council was set up
in 1992.
</P>
<P>
During today's meeting, Zou said that developing railway
transportation is an important way to advance the nation's
economy, and that Chinese transportation is developing rapidly,
but that "transporting by rail still constitutes an important part
of China's transportation service."
</P>
<P>
Economic cooperation and exchanges between China and the rest
of the world have been increasing since the country initiated its
reform and opening-up policy, Zou said, meaning a greater need for
increased transport capacity. He expressed the hope that friendly
cooperation between Chinese and foreign transport industries can
continue to grow.
</P>
<P>
Zou also briefed the guests on reforms and construction work in
China's railway transport.
</P>
<P>
Anatoly Zaitsev, the Council's President and Russian minister
of Railroads, said the Railway Cooperation Organization is willing
to cooperate with its Chinese counterpart, in order to enhance
friendship and improve each other's economy.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Minister of Railways Han Zhubin attended the meeting.
</P>
