<HEADLINE> Liberia Won't Be Used to Destabilize W. Africa: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, April 10 (Xinhua) -- The West African peacekeeping
force known as ECOMOG has vowed not to allow anyone to use the
territory of Liberia as a staging post to destabilize any
neighboring countries.
</P>
<P>
According to Daily Times today, ECOMOG Force Commander
Major-General Victor Malu was dispelling rumours about
disgruntled Guineans using Liberia as a base for rebel
activities.
</P>
<P>
"No armed group would be allowed to come together with the aim
of attacking another country from Liberia," he said at a meeting
with a delegation of the German Government Technical Cooperation
in Monrovia, the Liberian capital, on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The German organization is to open an office in Liberia soon
to help in the resettlement of the returning Liberian refugees
and reintegration of the former fighters.
</P>
<P>
According to the general, the current deployment of ECOMOG
troops in all the 13 counties in Liberia, which has greatly
enhanced the force's ability to dominate the security situation
in the country, is being done with special attention to most of
the border areas.
</P>
<P>
Malu also appealed to the international community to show more
pity for the misfortune of the teeming ex-combatants in Liberia
by accelerating efforts to rehabilitate and reintegrate them into
the mainstream of the Liberia society.
</P>
<P>
The integration of the more than 30,000 former factional
fighters disarmed would enhance the efforts to achieve a return
of total normalcy to Liberia, he said.
</P>
<P>
The present situation where a substantial number of disarmed
fighters mill around was unhealthy for the country, he warned.
</P>
<P>
The Nigerian general also assured full ECOMOG support to any
organization willing to help Liberians in this regard. 
</P>
</TEXT>
