Vancouver, Canada, this autumn, a TDC spokesman said here today.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that more than 20 leading suppliers of
software products will appear in the Hong Kong Pavilion at the
1997 edition of the exhibition from September 7 to 10 in
Vancouver.
</P>
<P>
Softworld '97 is a unique annual business-to-business deal
making occasion for software companies, suppliers, service
providers and investors.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong's software and related services market grew by 25
percent and 19 percent in 1994 and 1995 respectively and is
expected to continue to post double-digit growth this year.
</P>
<P>
Alan Wong, assistant executive director, said that TDC's
participation in Softworld '97 is a key project of the TDC's
promotion work this year to accelerate the development of the
software industry.
</P>
<P>
He said global demand for Hong Kong's software products is
continuing to surge and the Softworld '97 will provide a golden
opportunity for Hong Kong companies to network with potential
partners from around the world.
</P>
<P>
He said Hong Kong will host a half-day conference which will
promote Hong Kong as a strategic software partner.
</P>
<P>
Anthony Au, president of HKITF, said, "It gives us prime
exposure in events such as a Hong Kong Pavilion on software, an
International night co-hosted by Hong Kong, and priority for Hong
Kong companies to show their wares in the Seller's Forum."
</P>
