<HEADLINE> Internet Shopping Service Opens in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 10 (Xinhua) -- AEON World, an Internet
Shopping Service jointly run by AEON Credit Service (Asia) Co.
Ltd, IBM China-Hong Kong Corporation and Mitsubishi Corporation
(Hong Kong) Ltd., opened in Hong Kong this week.
</P>
<P>
As the first Internet Shopping mall in Asia and Pacific region,
AEON World is built and managed by IBM with AEON Credit Service
handling the marketing and clearing function for the transactions
process. Mitsubishi Corporation will cooperate in the recruitment
of merchants to the mall.
</P>
<P>
AEON World has attracted a number of shopping companies
including Jusco Department Store, Yaohan Best (electronics), City
Super, Challenger (car beauty and maintenance service), Fujitsu
(software and personal computers) and A Andrews (catalog sales).
</P>
<P>
Yoshiaki Ishii, chairman and managing director of Mitsubishi
Corporation (HK) Ltd., said that AEON world is introducing a new
era of shopping in Hong Kong as it combines the excitement of
shopping in Hong Kong with the convenience of the desktop
computer.
</P>
<P>
He said that it provides Hong Kong's shoppers with access to a
range of shops with all the convenience over the Internet 24 hours
a day.
</P>
<P>
Once a customer makes his purchase, the payment transaction
will be automatically handled by the merchant and the clearing
bank and no additional action is required by the customer, he
said.
</P>
<P>
Financial transactions of the AEON World will be handled
through Secure Electronic Transaction (SET), a complex encryption
procedure allowing the credit card payment to pass through the
clearing bank in a secure environment.  
</P>
</TEXT>
