<HEADLINE> Pakistan, U.S. Sign Air Traffic Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan and the United States
today signed an air traffic agreement aiming to expand cooperation
in this field between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Pakistani Secretary of Defense Hassan Raza Pasha and the U.S.
Ambassador to Pakistan Thomas W. Simons formally singed the
agreement on behalf of their respective countries in Rawalpindi,
sister city of Islamabad.
</P>
<P>
The new agreement entitled each country to designate any number
of airlines to conduct international air transportation between
Pakistan and the United States.
</P>
<P>
The agreement also allowed pure cargo flights anywhere in the
two countries.  
</P>
</TEXT>
