<HEADLINE> Mauritian Foreign Minister Visits Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Mauritian Minister of Foreign
Affairs, International and Regional Cooperation Paul Berenger
arrived here today on a 4-day visit to Sri Lanka.
</P>
<P>
Berenger, who is also deputy prime minister of Mauritius, is
the current chairman of the Indian Ocean Rim Association for
Regional Cooperation, of which the Sri Lankan foreign minister is
one of the two vice chairmen. The other is the Omani minister of
state for foreign affairs.
</P>
<P>
During his stay here, he is due to meet Prime Minister Sirimavo
Bandaranaike and other government ministers, according to official
sources here.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that he will hold talks with his Sri Lankan
counterpart Lakshman Kadirgamar on bilateral relations and issues
of common interest.
</P>
<P>
He is also expected to deliver a talk on "the Indian Ocean Rim
and Future Prospects" in Colombo.  
</P>
