<HEADLINE> ASEAN FMs to Meet for Discussing Entry of Myanmar, </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, April 10 (Xinhua) -- The foreign ministers of the
Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) will hold an
informal meeting here at the end of May to discuss the entry of
Myanmar, Cambodia and Laos into the regional grouping.
</P>
<P>
This was disclosed by Malaysian Foreign Minister Abdullah Ahmad
Badawi today upon his return from New Delhi where the ASEAN
foreign ministers, who attended the 12th Non-Aligned Movement
(NAM) Foreign Ministers' conference, had an informal meeting.
</P>
<P>
"We will also discuss preparations for the ASEAN summit here in
September and the 30th ASEAN anniversary celebrations," he said.
</P>
<P>
The meeting would also consider the need for an increase in the
allocation to the ASEAN Secretariat in Jakarta in view of its
expanding workload, according to the minister.
</P>
<P>
He said the ASEAN foreign ministers were also happy with the
preparation for their formal meeting here in July.  
</P>
