<HEADLINE> Uganda on Alert Against Rinderpest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Uganda is to vaccinate its cattle
nationwide to prevent the spread of rinderpest which kills cows and
buffaloes in Kenya and Tanzania now, ''the New Vision'' today quoted
a senior official as saying.
</P>
<P>
Kezimbira Muyingo, the State Minister for Agriculture in charge of
Animal Husbandary, told a press conference Tuesday that the disease
could spread into the country if measures were not taken now.
</P>
<P>
He said the vaccination will start from border areas.
Vaccinated animals will be marked to ensure none is missed.
</P>
<P>
He also appealed for ristricted movement of cattles from one area
to another to minimise the possibility of the desease-spreading.
</P>
<P>
But he assured there is no clue of the desease in north-eastern
Karamoja region.
</P>
<P>
There were rumours that rinderpest hit the north-east following
the Kenyan border residents pastured their cattles in the north-east
last dry season beginning from last November.
</P>
<P>
Veterinary surveys show there is no clinical signs of the disease,
he said.
</P>
<P>
The disease hit Uganda in 1945, 1906 and 1890. enditem

