<HEADLINE> Angolan Unity Govt Beneficial to Southern Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, April 19 (Xinhua) -- A government of national unity in
Angola, to be sworn in here tomorrow, will be beneficial to the
southern African region, visiting Mozambican Prime Minister
Pascoal Mocumbi said here today.
</P>
<P>
Mocumbi arrived at Luanda on Wednesday night to attend the
swearing-in ceremony of the Angolan new government.
</P>
<P>
The Mozambican prime minister said Angola's step from war to
peace would help create a sound environment for the development
and economic integrity of the southern African region.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Portuguese President Jorge Sampaio, who had also
arrived in Luanda on Wednesday night, said the peace process in
the country is "unreversable".
</P>
<P>
The Angolan parliament, participated in by both ruling and
opposition parties of the country, had been established on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
And an agreement over the power-sharing between the ruling
party and the opposition has been finally ironed out. 
</P>
