<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran's Resumption of Ties with US </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 10 (Xinhua) -- A candidate for Iranian
presidential election has said that resumptions of relations
between Iran and the United States was possible if he won the
elections.
</P>
<P>
Heshmatollah Tabarzadi, Secretary General of the Islamic
Students Coalition, made the statement in a front-page story
carried today by the official English daily Tehran Times.
</P>
<P>
Observers here noted that the statement by Tabarzadi reflects
the view and desire of the majority of the people, especially the
young people.
</P>
<P>
Iran's presidential election, the 7th one since the founding of
the Islamic Republic of Iran in 1979, is scheduled to be held on
May 23.
</P>
<P>
Tabarzadi said that Iran can have relations with all
countries that have not declared war against it, even the United
States, in accordance with the Constitution.
</P>
<P>
"If we set up a powerful government, we will be able to have
appropriate relations with the United States in line with our
national interests," he said.
</P>
<P>
He underlined that the United States and the Western media
should not be allowed to launch disinformation campaign against
Iran at international arena.
</P>
<P>
However, he admitted, Iran's relations with certain countries
are not cordial at present and "we should not provide our
enemies with excuses, turning our friends into enemies."
</P>
<P>
In February, Iranian President Hashemi Rafsanjani announced
Iran's policy toward the United States, saying that Iran seeks
no dialogue, no confrontation with the United States.
</P>
<P>
Tehran and Washington broke diplomatic ties shortly after
Iran's Islamic Revolution in 1979 and the two countries have since
then been hostile to each other over almost all issues.
</P>
<P>
The United States pursues a dual-containment policy toward
Iran and Iraq. It has imposed sanction on Iran and even
threatened to launch military strike against Iranian 19 targets,
including "terrorist" training camps and nuclear reactors.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
