<HEADLINE> Manila City Jail Inmates Undergo Skills Training </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 10 (Xinhua) -- A total of 109 inmates of the
Manila City Jail have started a one-month free technical skills
training inside the jail compound, the Bureau of Jail Management
and Penology announced today.
</P>
<P>
Director of the bureau Silas Laurio said the training program
is part of the bureau's program thrusts to rehabilitate inmates
while in confinement to prepare them to become productive citizens
following their release from custody.
</P>
<P>
Laurio said that since April 7, 53 inmates are studying basic
radio electronics, 45 are taking up cosmetology courses while the
remaining 11 take up rugmaking inside the jail compound.
</P>
<P>
"This is the bureau's way of reforming and rehabilitating
inmates while in confinement to prepare them for their eventual
immersion in the community after serving their time in jail," he
said.
</P>
<P>
Lauiro said more skills training programs will be undertaken in
the other city, municipal and district jails throughout the
country.  
</P>
</TEXT>
