<HEADLINE> Share Prices Fall on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Share prices continued to
declined in dull trading on the Singapore market as the benchmark
Straits Times Industrials Index fell by 15.93 points to close at
2,087.27 points today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume shrank to 91.7 million units, valued at
243.03 million Singapore dollars (about 168.77 million US
dollars). Declines overwhelmed advances by 239 to 79, while 288
other counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong Land was the most actively traded stock as it
registered a turnover of 4.23 million units. It was followed by
Public Bank Foreign which had 3.33 million units traded, while
Westmont Land saw 3.22 million of its shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
Malaya Banking 200 led the gainers of the day as it rose by 30
cents to finish at 15.3 Singapore dollars. Robinson increased by
20 cents to end at 6.8 Singapore dollars, while JC-MPH warrants
gained 16 cents to close at 0.76 dollar.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Asean Fund was the biggest loser as it
declined by 1.3 dollars to end at 16.5 US dollars. Van Der Hurst
warrant 98 fell by 1.1 Singapore dollars to finish at 3.6
Singapore dollars. City Developments ended 50 cents lower at 13.2
Singapore dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
