<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Customs officials at Germany's
Duesseldorf airport today discovered about 22 kilograms of cocaine
in an unclaimed suitcase, worth about 3.5 million marks (2 million
U.S. dollars) on the black market, press reports said.
</P>
<P>
The suitcase came on a flight from the Caribbean island of
Curacao. The police are searching for the owner who is believed to
have deserted the suitcase for fear of passing customs control
with the drug. 
