<HEADLINE> ADB Grants Technical Aid to Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 10 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank (ADB)
has decided to extend a financial support of 314,000 US dollars as
technical assistance for the agrarian reform communities in the
Philippines.
</P>
<P>
Agrarian Reform Secretary Ernesto Garilao said his department
will be the executive agency for this assistance which will be
implemented over a four-month period, the Philippine News Agency
reported today.
</P>
<P>
Garilao said that the technical assistance will benefit about
100 agrarian reform communities out of the total 863 agrarian
communities nationwide set up under the government's Comprehensive
Agrarian Reform Program.
</P>
<P>
The technical assistance will also address coordination between
the agrarian reform programs and projects supported by government
agencies and different donors, Garilao said.  
</P>
