<HEADLINE> Beijing to Hold Tulip Show </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Residents of the Chinese capital
will be able to see Netherlands' world-famous tulips without going
abroad at a one-month show, which will open Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The exhibit will be held in Zhongshan Park, which is adjacent
to the Forbidden City in the heart of Beijing. More than 500,000
colorful tulips will be arranged in ten big floral mosaics,
bearing both Chinese and Dutch characteristics.
</P>
<P>
In addition, over 6,000 blooming peonies, azaleas, Chinese
herbaceous peonies and orchids and their Dutch equivalents are
expected to be favorites at the park.
</P>
<P>
It is the second time that Zhongshan Park, in cooperation with
Holland Euro-Asia Flower Group, has held the tulip show. The
organizers displayed some 70 varieties of tulips during the same
period last year, and the exhibition later toured in 13 Chinese
cities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
