<HEADLINE> Chinese President to Visit Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Chineses President Jiang Zemin
will pay a state visit to Russia from April 22 to 26 at the
invitation of Russian President Boris Nikolayevich Yeltsin.
</P>
<P>
The announcement was made by Chinese Foreign Ministry Spokesman
Shen Guofang at a routine press conference here today.
</P>
<P>
The Spokesman said, this will be the fourth summit meeting
between the two countries in recent years and also the first since
the announcement of the establishment of their strategic
coordinative partnership.
</P>
<P>
"The leaders of the two countries will have an in-depth
exchange of views on ways to deepen the friendly and good
neighborly relations between China and Russia and major
international issues of mutual interest," he said, adding that the
two sides will issue a joint statement on international
situation. "This visit will further facilitate the development of
the bilateral relations between the two countries," the spokesman
stressed.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, President Jiang Zemin will also sign,
together with the heads of state of Russia, Kazakhstan,
Kirghizstan and Tadzhikistan, the agreement on the mutual
reduction of military forces in border areas, he disclosed, adding
that the agreement will not only contribute to the further
development of the friendly and good-neighborly relations and
cooperation between China and the four countries, but also serve
peace, security and stability of the Asia-Pacific region and the
world at large.  
</P>
