<HEADLINE> Foreign Expertise Gives Helping Hand to Liaoning's Agriculture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Panjin City in northeast China's
Liaoning Province, a clam production base in the country, has made
a breakthrough in the artificial cultivation of the clams with the
help of a Japanese expert.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, the province has been active in introducing
foreign expertise for agricultural development.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, foreign experts were involved in more than 42
agricultural projects in the province, according to the provincial
office in charge of the introduction of foreign
expertise. Emphasis was placed on corn, rice, vegetables and
animal husbandry.
</P>
<P>
Some 13,200 ha of potatoes was grown in Jianping County in the
province, producing 18,750 kg of potatoes per ha. Under the
instruction of a French potato expert, the per ha yield in the
pilot field rose to 31,500 kg. The county's output value brought
by the potatoes is expected to increase by 180 million yuan if the
technique is applied in all the fields. 
</P>
</TEXT>
