<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dalian Becomes a Favorable Beach-side Tourist Destination </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Dalian in northeast China, has
become one of the most attractive beach-side tourist destinations
in China.
</P>
<P>
Over 1,900 kilometers of coastal line and 170 islets grant
unique beach-side scenery to Dalian where there are two national
scenic areas, a national holiday resort, and two provincial
holiday resorts.
</P>
<P>
The Jinshitan National Holiday Resort is one of the country's
upmarket attractions, where travelers can not only enjoy golden
beaches, but can also golf, cruise, and go hunting.
</P>
<P>
With the opening of the Ice Ravine Tourist Area in the north,
where ice lantern shows are put up, the summer resort has also
become hot to tourists in winter.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the military port of Lushun was opened to tourists,
to the delight of those curious about this port where the
Sino-Japanese War of 1894-95 was fought.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the city played host to over 160,000 tourists from
128 countries and regions, plus 15 million domestic tourists.
</P>
<P>
Tourism earned the city 160 million US dollars and over 4.1
billion yuan (493.9 million US dollars) last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
