<HEADLINE> Tanzania Starts to Issue Visas at Entry Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, April 10 (Xinhua) -- The Tanzanian authority
started to issue visitors visa at the entry points in a step to
promote tourism by relaxing travel and visa regulations, the
local paper "Express" reported today.
</P>
<P>
Minister for Tourism and Natural Resources Zakia Meghji said
this has been applied to tourists staying in Tanzania between
seven to 90 days.
</P>
<P>
In the past, tourist companies, airlines and hotel firms have
had complained of persisting bureaucracy at the entry points,
mainly the Dar es Salaam and Kilimanjaro international airports
where tourists were turned back to their countries of origin for
lacking visas. 
