<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Foreign Minister Meets Syrian Vice-President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier and Foreign
Minister Qian Qichen stressed here today that the key to the
resolution of the Middle East issue lies in the Israeli retreat
from the occupied Arab lands and the resumption of the Palestinian
people's national rights, including the right to set up an
independent Palestine.
</P>
<P>
Qian made the remarks during his talks with the First
Vice-President of Syria Abdel Halim Khaddam in the Diaoyutai State
Guest House here today.
</P>
<P>
He said that Israel's move to expand the Jewish settlement in
eastern Jerusalem violates relevant resolutions of the United
Nations and is one of the causes of the downturn in the Middle
East peace process.
</P>
<P>
He said that China is greatly concerned about this
situation. China believes that the principle of "land for peace"
is a common view reached by all parties of the Middle East and
should be maintained in the future, he said.
</P>
<P>
The realization of comprehensive and fair peace in the Middle
East conforms with the fundamental interests of the people in the
territory and is beneficial to world peace and development, he
said.
</P>
<P>
He said that China supports Syria in its efforts to recover the
Golan Height through political discussion. China believes that
Syria's request to resume peace talks on the basis of the progress
that has been made during Syrian-Israeli talks is reasonable, he
said.
</P>
<P>
China wishes that all parties involved in the Middle East issue
will adopt a practical and flexible attitude to resume talks on
the basis of the principle of "land for peace" and relevant UN
resolutions, in order to revitalize the peace process, he said.
</P>
<P>
He said that China is ready to join the international community
to contribute to a comprehensive and fair resolution of the Middle
East issue.
</P>
<P>
Khaddam briefed Qian about the current situation in the Middle
East. He said that at present, the peace process has come to a
standstill, posing a threat to peace and stability in the
territory.
</P>
<P>
He said that Syria wishes to continue the peace process in
light of relevant UN resolutions and the principle of "land for
peace." He wishes that China, a permanent member of the UN
Security Council, will play a greater role in promoting peace and
stability in the Middle East.
</P>
<P>
The two sides changed views on the friendly cooperative
relations between the two countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
