<DOCNO> XIE19970410.0184 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> IPU Conference Opens in Seoul </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, April 10 (Xinhua) -- The 97th conference of
Inter-Parliamentary Union (IPU) opened here today with more than
600 parliamentarians from 130 countries seeking ways to enhance
cooperation for international and regional security and stability.
</P>
<P>
Organized by the IPU, the world organization of parliaments,
the conference held it's opening ceremony at the Seoul Sejong
Culture Center this morning.
</P>
<P>
South Korean President Kim Young-sam attended the ceremony and
declared the opening of the conference.
</P>
<P>
In his welcoming speech, President Kim emphasized the need of
harmony and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Speakers at the ceremony included Kim Soo-han, speaker of the
host National Assembly, and Ahmed Fathy Sorour, president of the
Inter-Parliamentary Council, the IPU's governing body, Adrianus
Mooy, special representative of United Nation Secretary-General
Kofia Annan.
</P>
<P>
A Chinese delegation led by Wang Guangying, vice-chairman of
the Standing Committee of the National People's Congress, attended
the opening ceremony.
</P>
<P>
During the six-day conference scheduled to end on April 15,
various IPU committees will meet to deal with main topics of world
and regional security and stability as well as other topics, such
as taking measures to change production and consumption patterns
for sustainable development.
</P>
<P>
In a pre-conference meeting held Wednesday, more than 100
female legislators discussed in particular the theme: education as
a means to prevent the sexual exploitation of children.
</P>
<P>
The IPU has a current membership of 135 national parliaments
worldwide. The number will increase during the Seoul session when
the requests for membership from the parliaments of Cambodia,
Georgia and Tajikistan are accepted.
</P>
<P>
South Korea joined the Union in 1964 and hosted the conference
in 1983 for the first time. 
</P>
</TEXT>
