<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, April 10 (Xinhua) -- A foreign trade fair aimed at
enhancing economic ties between China's island province of Hainan
and Vietnam has ended recently, generating a total of one billion
yuan-worth of contracts.
</P>
