<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Younger Readers to Know Old International Friends </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Younger readers in China will be
able to learn the lives of 11 renowned international friends of
the country through a set of newly published books.
</P>
<P>
The 11 books, under the general title of "Friends of the
Chinese people," tell the stories of 11 international notables
who have or had made outstanding contributions to China.
</P>
<P>
The books were jointly composed and published by the Chinese
People's Association for Friendship with Foreign Countries and the
Hebei Children's Publishing House.
</P>
<P>
They include Edgar Snow, the American author of Red Star Over
China, and Norman Bethune, and a Canadian doctor who was highly
praised by the late Chairman Mao Zedong for his selfless devotion
to the Chinese people's War Against Japanese Aggression
(1937-1945).
</P>
<P>
The books are designed to tell the younger generation about
the past and help enhance their sense of internationalism and
patriotism.
</P>
<P>
Su Fei, wife of late George Hatem about whom one of the books
is dedicated, told a forum in the Diaoyutai State Guest House
marking the books' publication today that it requires a great deal
of will power to be a long-time friend of China.
</P>
<P>
"In the past 60 years, our life has been closely associated
with the twists and turns of the nation's fate. There was a lot of
happiness, excitement and, of course, pains," she said.
</P>
<P>
"But we believe that we have chosen the right course in life,"
she said.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Premier and Foreign Minister Qian Qichen also made a
speech at the meeting. He said that China is ready to establish
and develop friendly cooperative relations with as many countries
as possible in the world.
</P>
<P>
He said that China pays close attention to increasing
people-to-people contacts with other countries, because this will
help to create a fine environment for the country's reform,
opening up, and modernization drive, he said.
</P>
<P>
He said that China sincerely cherishes its gratitude to and
memories of the international friends who shared weal and woe with
Hebei Children's Publishing House.
</P>
<P>
Diplomatic envoys to China from Austria, Britain, Canada,
India, New Zealand, and Russia attended the forum.  
</P>
</TEXT>
