Syrian people to develop the friendly cooperation between the two
countries in various fields on the basis of equality, mutual
benefit and mutual respect.
</P>
<P>
Rong made the remark during a meeting with Syrian
Vice-President Abdel Halim Khaddam, who arrived here Wednesday on
a working visit to China at the invitation of the Chinese
Government.
</P>
<P>
Rong said the exchange of visits between leaders of the two
countries is conducive to their mutual understanding and the
growth of friendly relations and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Rong described Khaddam, who has been to China a number of
times, as an old friend of the Chinese people. He said Syria is
one of the earliest arab countries to forge diplomatic ties with
China, and in the past four decades and more, their friendly
cooperation has been steadily developing.
</P>
<P>
China cherishes its friendship with Syria and pays great
attention to the development of the bilateral relations, the
Chinese vice-president stressed.
</P>
<P>
Rong thanked Syria for backing China in human rights matters
and holding the "one China" position on the Taiwan issue. The
Chinese people support the Syrian people in their struggle to
maintain national sovereignty and territorial integrity, he added.
</P>
<P>
Khaddam said China, a friend of Syria, is playing an important
role in the world. It is important to strengthen the cooperation
and coordination between Syria and China, he said.
</P>
<P>
The human rights issue is now used by some western countries as
an excuse to interfere in the internal affairs of other countries,
Khaddam pointed out, and his country supports China in fighting
against such interference in the name of human rights.
</P>
<P>
Syria stands with China in its efforts for peaceful
reunification of its motherland, Khaddam added.
</P>
<P>
The two vice-presidents also exchanged views on the Middle East
situation.  
</P>
</TEXT>
