<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Proprietors and Partners Flourish in Jilin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Proprietorships and private
businesses in northeast China's Jilin Province grew rapidly last
year.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1996, individually-run businesses exceeded one
million, up 11.3 percent from the previous year, while that of
privately-run firms rose to 19,000, a 18.5 percent increase.
</P>
<P>
The two sectors employed 1.82 million workers, accounting for
5.4 percent of the total workforce in Jilin. Newly employed
workers include 140,000 laid-off by state-owned enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Last Year, individually or privately-run firms turned to the
local government 700 million yuan in taxes, making up one tenth of
the total industrial and commercial tax income in the province.
</P>
<P>
The economic zones dominated by individually-run firms have
expanded from 40 to 96. The number of technology-intensive
enterprises have increased from 4,800 to 69,000.
</P>
<P>
Firms engaging in agriculture and aquatic cultivation grew from
90,000 in 1995 to the present 210,000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
