<HEADLINE> Overseas Chinese Donate for South China's Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, April 10 (Xinhua) -- South China's Guangdong
Province has received donations valued at some 3.2 billion yuan
(about 400 million US dollars) annually from overseas Chinese in
the past few years, according to the latest statistics.
</P>
<P>
Official figures show that more than 95 percent of the gifts
are in kind, such as teaching facilities, medical equipment,
books, and industrial and agricultural machinery.
</P>
<P>
About 25 percent of the donations are for industry and
agriculture, 20 percent for cultural and educational development,
10 percent for public health, and 15 percent for social welfare,
said an official with the provincial government.
</P>
<P>
"Most of the overseas Chinese's donations go to their
hometowns," the official noted, adding that in some regions almost
every town has schools and hospitals backed by the overseas
Chinese.  
