<HEADLINE> Commercial Bank on Track </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, April 10 (Xinhua) -- China Merchant Bank, the first
private commercial bank in China, has increased its assets to
nearly 103 billion yuan by 1996, from the 100 million yuan
starting-point ten years ago.
</P>
<P>
The bank has realized nearly six billion yuan in profits since
its was set up a decade ago and ranked the 11th in actual profit
growth among the world's 1,000 biggest banks.
</P>
<P>
Starting from a small and local commercial bank, the China
Merchant Bank spared no single effort in the past ten years to
improve its management methods, prevent lending risks through
stronger supervision of credit-granting, and attract a team of
experienced and highly-educated financial talents, said a senior
official from the bank.
</P>
<P>
Financial innovation was another important means in our bank's
quick expansion, the official said, pointing to the fact that the
China Merchant Bank was a leader in opening offshore financial
services and a full line of other new services to attract more
clients.
</P>
<P>
As a result, the bank's deposits and outstanding loans have
been growing at an average annual rate of 61.9 and 54.4 percent in
the past decade.
</P>
<P>
Based in southern city of Shenzhen, the bank already opened 11
branches nationwide and representative offices in Beijing and Hong
Kong. It has also established agent bank relationships with more
than 600 banks all over the world. 
</P>
</TEXT>
