<HEADLINE> Scenic West Lake Becomes Greener </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Newly-planted trees and flowers
are adding charm to the picturesque West Lake, one of the top
tourist attractions in China.
</P>
<P>
Since spring, a popular tourist season at the lake, located in
Hangzhou, capital of east China's Zhejiang province, over 43,600
trees and flowers have been planted around the water.
</P>
<P>
In order to greet the crowds of tourists, environmental workers
launched a clean-up campaign focusing on the entire lake
area. Over 130 benches have been added around the lake to enable
visitors to enjoy the scenery in comfort.
</P>
<P>
Efforts have also been made to ensure the smooth drainage of
wastewater from the lake, sources said.
</P>
<P>
A number of tourist hotels located around the lake have also
been renovated in preparation of the tourist inflow, according to
hoteliers.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
