<HEADLINE> TV Program on Hong Kong Basic Law Shown </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, April 10 (Xinhua) -- A TV series on the Basic Law of
the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) is being shown
on cable television stations nationwide to welcome the return of
Hong Kong to the motherland on July 1.
</P>
<P>
The program was co-produced by the Xinhua News Agency Hong Kong
Branch, the city government of Shenzhen in south China's Guangdong
province, and the Shenzhen Cable Television Station.
</P>
<P>
The 50-part documentary explains the Basic Law in pictures and
simple language.
</P>
<P>
The Basic Law was drafted in accordance with the concept of
"one country two systems," set forth by late Chinese leader Deng
Xiaoping. Promulgated in 1990 after four-years of drafting, it
makes clear a series of fundamental principles and policies the
Chinese government will implement in Hong Kong after 1997.
</P>
<P>
The producers said that every Chinese should be acquainted
with the Basic Law, which will serve as the constitution of HK
after July 1, 1997.
</P>
<P>
The Basic Law maps out a blueprint of Hong Kong in various
aspects, ranging from politics to society, economy, legal system,
and way of life.
</P>
<P>
The producers added that video tapes and VCDs of the program
will be issued nationwide shortly. 
</P>
</TEXT>
