<HEADLINE> Thai Central Bank to Tighten Checks on Institutions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 10 (Xinhua) -- The Bank of Thailand wants to
ensure its methods of supervising financial institutions pinpoint
problems before they require drastic corrective action.
</P>
<P>
The Finance Ministry has formed a special working group to work
out ways to improve its system of checking the business procedures
and transactions of financial institutions, according to Permanent
Secretary M.R. Chatumongol Sonakul.
</P>
<P>
This method is accepted abroad as the best solution, but in
Thailand's case the central bank has never scrutinized financial
institutions' business processes, he said.
</P>
<P>
The government's financial master plan for 1995-2000 calls for
an improvement in the capital adequacy ratio of financial
institutions, greater provision for doubtful debt, and a more
accurate way of calculating the risk from foreign exchange dealing
and borrowing.  
</P>
