<HEADLINE> Klima Elected SPO Chairman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, April 9 (Xinhua) -- Austria's Federal Chancellor Viktor
Klima was officially elected chairman of the ruling Social
Democratic Party (SPO) at the party's congress today.
</P>
<P>
Klima has been prime minister and acting party chairman since
Franz Vranitzky stepped down in January, after 10 years in the
job, over growing disagreements between his party and its
coalition partner, the Austrian People's Party (OVP).
</P>
<P>
Eight vice chairmen, the presidium and an executive committee
of the party were also elected at the one-day congress, held in
the western city of Linz.
</P>
<P>
Klima, who was finance minister before gaining the top job,
told the congress that full employment was the SPO's top
objective, and said the right to work was every citizen's human
right.
</P>
<P>
On security, the new chairman ruled out the possibility of
Austria joining the North Atlantic Treaty Organization, as the OVP
has demanded. He said that membership of the military alliance
would go against the country's policy of neutrality.
</P>
<P>
Klima also assured the meeting his government would not raise
interest rates in the near future, saying they were high enough.
</P>
<P>
The congress, with the slogan "March to the New Century,"
hailed Vranitzky's 10-year contribution to the party with a
standing ovation after he finished his farewell speech. 
</P>
</TEXT>
