<HEADLINE> Illegally Traded Logs Seized in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, April 10 (Xinhua) -- A total of 76.9 tons of illegally
traded logs and sawn timber were seized by the Myanmar forestry
authorities from saw mill owners in the country's Bago division,
the official newspaper New Light of Myanmar reported today.
</P>
<P>
The illegal logs and sawn timber were confiscated by the
state-run Forestry Department Head Office from four saw mill
owners in villages in the Thonze township of the division last
Friday.
</P>
<P>
Action was being taken against the four according to Myanmar's
Forest Law, which was enacted in 1992, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Since then, Myanmar has restricted export of logs, banning the
private sector exporting teak logs.
</P>
<P>
