<HEADLINE> Malaysia Willing to Help Pakistan Increase Exports: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, April 10, (Xinhua) -- Malaysian Prime Minister
Mahathir Mohamad said his country can help Pakistan increase its
exports and reduce its imports.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a press conference here Wednesday evening before his
departure to Kuala Lumpur, Mahathir said his country could help
Pakistan boost its exports by processing its food products, which
would earn Pakistan more foreign exchange.
</P>
<P>
Both sides can also discuss ways as to how Malaysia could be of
help to Pakistan to slash the latter's imports, he said.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia was looking into areas like oil and gas exploration,
building pipelines and power generation, where it could have close
cooperation with Pakistan, he said.
</P>
<P>
During his hour-long talks with his Pakistani counterpart Nawaz
Sharif, Mahathir said their discussion revolved around matters of
development, privatization, downsizing of the Government,
reduction of trade deficit and foreign investment.
</P>
<P>
On the trade imbalance which is tilted heavily in favor of
Malaysia, he said his country could identify what it could buy
from Pakistan to reduce it.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan's efforts to become a member of ASEAN, he said, did
figure during his talks with Sharif and his country would support
Pakistan in this regard.  
</P>
