<HEADLINE> Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia believes that there was
no need to worry about the relationship between Indonesia and Hong
Kong after the latter's return to China later this year, an
Indonesian diplomat said.
</P>
<P>
The Indonesian Deputy Consul General in Hong Kong, Suhadi
Salam, said on Tuesday in Hong Kong that the relations between the
two sides would remain stable after the Hong Kong's handover to
China, Antara news agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
China and Indonesia have agreed that the Indonesian consulate
general in Hong Kong would remain after the handover on July 1, he
said.
</P>
<P>
Economic cooperation between Hong Kong and Indonesia has been
increasing, marked by continued visits by Hong Kong businessmen to
the country.
</P>
<P>
From 1992 to 1996, over 260 Hong Kong businessmen visited
Indonesia. Hong Kong has made investment worth 18.567 billion U.S.
dollars in 356 projects in the country since 1967, making it the
third biggest investor in Indonesia after Japan and Britain, he
said.
</P>
<P>
After the handover, Indonesia will seek new areas of
cooperation with Hong Kong, he said.  
</P>
