<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sino-Italian Firm Making Ozone-Safe Compressors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Zanussi Elettromeccanic Tianjin
Compressor Co. Ltd, the first firm in China to manufacture
CFC-free refrigerator compressors, will expand its production
capacity.
</P>
<P>
The sino-Italian joint venture plans to expand its annual
production capacity to three million compressors including
CFC-free R134a compressors by 2000 from present one million units,
according to today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
The number of R134a compressors is expected to meet part of the
growing demand in the domestic refrigerator industry, which is
working to phase out CFCs as cooling agents in accordance with
international environment protection efforts.
</P>
<P>
CFC - chlorofluorocarbon - is an ozone-depleting chemical
compound containing freon that is used as a cooling agent.
</P>
<P>
Many countries have banned the use of CFC because freon is
suspected of playing a role in the destruction of the atmosphere's
ozone layer, which protects the environment from direct exposure
to ultraviolet sun rays.
</P>
<P>
Chinese government has promised to phase out CFCs by 2005.
</P>
<P>
Domestic refrigerator manufacturers used more than 12 million
compressors in 1996, including more than two million CFC-free
compressors. Now, almost all of the CFC-free compressors are
imported. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
