<HEADLINE> Academy to Strengthen Reform </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 10 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Academy of Sciences
(CAS), the country's top scientific body, has called on its over
100 research institutes to re-orient their research according to
the country's current strategy on scientific development.
</P>
<P>
Today's China Daily said that CAS, meanwhile, is set to start
re-identifying the 120 institutes' research programs in the next
three years.
</P>
<P>
"All the institutes should have their fixed position on science
research and technology development," said Lu Yongxiang,
vice-president of CAS, at its annual meeting which closed
yesterday.
</P>
<P>
"In 1997, we will begin to identify 10 to 15 institutes'
research fields. Once their research direction was clarified and
approved, they would have more financial support."
</P>
<P>
Lu said that CAS will deepen its reform to help the academy
become a science research base of world level, an education base
for young scientists and a base of high-tech development.
</P>
<P>
"But some of the institutes dispersed their research force on
research projects out of their essential field and lose the
advantage of the institute," Lu said, "We need to gather our
research force on the research to benefit the nation's social and
economic development."
</P>
<P>
As one way, CAS will try to combine its 120 institutes into 80
institutes.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
