<HEADLINE> China Develops Organic Food Industry on Island </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 10 (Xinhua) -- The State Planning Commission has
approved a massive national-level pesticide-free food program on
Chongming Island, China's third largest.
</P>
<P>
A 32,000-hectare production center will be built on the island
in north Shanghai, to produce organic food, which is supposed to
be insecticide-free and good for health, according to a local
official.
</P>
<P>
The Chongming County government and an agro-business group from
Shanghai will work together to build the island into the nation's
top supplier of eels and crabs, and the biggest organic food
production center in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
"The production center is a substantial move in the island's
development strategy, and also a prelude to future massive
development," said the official.
</P>
<P>
Chongming island's focus is on economic development for the next
century, after the Pudong New Area in east Shanghai. Its clean
environment and rich farming resources make it an ideal site to
develop "clean" industrialized agriculture. 
</P>
</TEXT>
