<HEADLINE> Dortmund Defeats United 1-0 in Euro Champions Cup Semis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, April 9 (Xinhua) -- Borussia Dortmund of Germany
overwhelmed Manchester United of England 1-0 in the first leg
semi-finals of the European Champions Cup soccer tournament in
Dortmunt, Germany on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Rene Tretschok, Dortmund's second-choice forward, struck a
deflected winner in the 75th minute of the match after teammate
Nicky Butt hit a post.
</P>
<P>
Manchester United, which started without goalkeeper Peter
Schmeichel, suffered another blow when midfielder Roy Keane picked
up his second booking of the tournament, ruling him out of the
return.
</P>
<P>
The English side, bidding to become the first English club to
reach the European Champions Cup final since Liverpool in 1985,
were forced to call up Dutchman Raimond van der Gouw as a
last-minute replacement for back injury victim Peter Schmeichel.
</P>
<P>
Dortmund commanded the midfield for the first 20 minutes with
Portugal's Paulo Sousa and Andreas Moller orchestrating their
forays into the rivals' territory.
</P>
<P>
The home side, playing in front of more than 48,000
spectators, were mostly kept at bay by an organized Manchester
United defence.
</P>
<P>
Keane earned a booking for a foul on Sousa and things got worse
for Manchester United as Tretschok, almost anonymous until then,
fired in a shot from distance that skewed off Gary Pallister past
Van der Gouw. It was only Tretschok's second goal in 21 European
matches.
</P>
<P>
Dortmund Police reported 73 arrests before the match, of which
38 were English soccer fans. 
</P>
</TEXT>
