<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Juventus Beats Ajax 2-1 in Euro Champions Cup Semis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, April 9 (Xinhua) -- Holders Juventus of Italy
defeated Ajax of the Netherlands 2-1 in the first leg semi-finals
of the European Champions Cup soccer tournament in Amsterdam,
Netherlands on Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
The match in Amsterdam was a re-run of last year's European
Champions Cup final.
</P>
<P>
Ajax, who lifted this trophy in 1995, was dominated by
Marcello Lippi's slick passing team from the start.
</P>
<P>
Juventus took the lead after 14 minutes when Vieri collected
the ball outside the area, pushed it foward for Vladimir Jugovic,
whose first-time flick found Amoruso unmarked.
</P>
<P>
Amoruso's shot hit the diving body of Ajax goalkeeper Edwin Van
der Saar but the goalkeeper could not keep the ball out.
</P>
<P>
In the 41th minute of the game, Vieri fired home a low shot
into the right-hand corner which caught Van der Saar completely
flat-footed.
</P>
<P>
