<HEADLINE> Gaumont Wins Ghent-Wavelgem Cycling Stage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, April 9 (Xinhua) -- Frenchman Philippe Gaumont headed
a sprint finish with a time of four hours 45 minutes contested by
about 20 riders to win the 208-kilometer Ghent-Wavelgem race on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Andrei Tchmil of Ukrainia finished second and Belgian Johan
Capiot came third.
</P>
<P>
Gaumont said he was now confident of doing well in Sunday's
Paris-Roubaix World Cup race.
</P>
<P>
Wednesday's race ended with a sprint after attempts by world
champion Johan Museeuw to break up the field in the hilly
Kemmelberg section of the race succeeded only in splitting the
pack into a large and small group. 
</P>
