<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, Apirl 9 (Xinhua) -- Sweden's defending champion
Thomas Enqvist conceded his opening match to German Rainer
Schuttler because of illness at the Gold Flake Open tennis
tournament in Madras on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Malivai Washington of the United States and Alex Radulescu of
Germany entered the quarter-finals.
</P>
<P>
Second seeded Enqvist pulled out of the match while tying the
German 6-6 in the first set, complaining of nausea.
</P>
<P>
Craig Gabriel, a spokesman for the ATP tournament, said Enqvist
had been suffering from nausea for the last three days but tried
his best to play the match. He was unable to carry on.
</P>
