<DOCNO> XIE19970410.0298 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> US Republicans Warn of Military Readiness Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 9 (xinhua) -- The Republicans today warned
that the U.S. military is plagued by overworked and undertrained
personnel and would be difficult to carry out another operation
like the Gulf War.
</P>
<P>
In a report on the U.S. military readiness, Republican Floyd
Spence, head of the House National Security Committee, said the
policy of cutting more personnel while committing to more
peacekeeping missions has undermined the military's fighting
abilities.
</P>
<P>
He warned that the U.S. couldn't today do another Gulf War-type
operation with the same efficiency.
</P>
<P>
"The reality is that years of declining defense budgets, a
smaller force structure...are stretching U.S. military forces to
the breaking point," he noted.
</P>
<P>
The report was concluded after Spence's committee members'
visits to more than 24 U.S. military installations over the past
seven months. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
