<HEADLINE> Wall Street Stocks Turn Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, April 9 (Xinhua) -- Stocks on Wall Street turned
lower today amid mounting concerns about an inflation report to be
out Friday.
</P>
<P>
Like Tuesday, the Dow Jones industrial average again traded
within a very narrow range until the final hour, but this time
sank to a drop of 45.32 points to 6,563.84, wiping out most of the
prior day's late advance.
</P>
<P>
Advancers outnumbered decliners by a slim margin on the New
York Stock Exchange, where volume totaled 451.49 million shares as
against 448.92 million in the previous session.
</P>
<P>
Other major indexes also turned lower as technology shares,
faltered after having recouped some losses over the past sessions.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500-stock list fell 5.52 to 760.60, and
the NYSE composite index fell 2.02 to 400.29.
</P>
<P>
The Nasdaq composite index fell 7.94 to 1,249.43, and the
American Stock Exchange composite index rose 1.56 to 562.98.
</P>
<P>
IBM, the Dow's strongest issue over the past two sessions,
pulled back sharply.
</P>
<P>
The markets have fallen amid fears the economy's vigorous
growth will aggravate inflationary pressures, prompting the
Federal Reserve to raise interest rates aggressively to slow the
economic pace. 
</P>
</TEXT>
