<HEADLINE> IDB Approves First Guarantee for Private Sector Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 9 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American Development
Bank (IDB) today announced the approval of its first guarantee for
private sector project in Latin America.
</P>
<P>
A 31.25 million U.S. dollar guarantee is provided to senior
debt note-holders investing in Bogotana de Aguas y Saneamiento
S.C.A., E.S.P. for a wastewater treatment plant serving the Bogota
area of Colombia.
</P>
<P>
The guarantee provides a component in the project financing
package that is expected to help make a private placement of debt
securities a success.
</P>
<P>
The plant, whose total cost is some 125 million dollars, is the
first phase of three projects designed to help clean up the Bogota
River which will be owned and operated by Bogotana de Aguas y
Saneamiento (BAS). After completion, it will be able to process
four cubic meters per second of wastewater and remove
sedimentation. Its phase II of the project will further purify the
water through secondary or biological treatment.
</P>
<P>
The IDB's partial political risk guarantee ensures compensation
to certain senior debt note-holders in case of an early termination
of the concession or in case of restrictions on foreign exchange
convertibility. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
