<HEADLINE> Rodionov Favors Russian-Chinese Relations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 9 (Xinhua) -- The increase of cooperation,
including the military, between Russia and China is not directed
against a third country, Russian Defense Minister Igor Rodionov
stated on Wednesday in an interview with Xinhua News Agency.
</P>
<P>
Before his visit to China scheduled for 13, April, Rodionov
said that the cooperation between Russia and China should be the
most favorable to the Asia and the Pacific region, and "can serve
as an example and beacon for other countries."
</P>
<P>
He believed that his visit to China must result in strong
impulse to deepen the bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
In reply to the question on military cooperation with China,
Rodionov cited a Russian diplomat as saying that "here flares up
an old love".
</P>
<P>
He said that for recent years Russia and China have signed a
number of important agreements, while military contacts between
the two countries have extended in the fields such as logistic
ensuring, connecxion, civil defense, topograph, military education
and science, medicine, building and billeting armed forces, as
well as space.
</P>
<P>
Rodionov meanwhile noted that the reform of national defense is
one of the urgent tasks in the cooperation between Russia and
China though the two countries are occupied by the serious reform
in other fields.
</P>
<P>
As for the prospects of the military cooperation with China the
minister said "I am optimistic enough for it. We have a great
potential of cooperation -- it is the most important -- the desire
to develop and strengthen the contacts in the interests of the two
peoples and two great countries, and for the mutual security.
</P>
<P>
Asked about the problems concerning the Russian military
reform, Rodionov said there should be no doubt of the reform, that
was required by the international and domestic situation.
</P>
<P>
The conception of the military reform has been worked out by
the Defense Ministry, the Headquarters of General Staff and the
Defense Council, the minister added.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that the definitive aim of the Russian military
reform is to enable the defense to have the proper reaction to all
the dangers threatening to Russia's safety, on conditions of
minimum expenditure.
</P>
<P>
The military reform should be conducted together with the
entier reform of the society, including the reform of all
strengthing departments, he said.
</P>
<P>
Rodionov told Xinhua that the Russian army is going to be
reduced by 200 thousands this year, but will increase its quality
and equipments. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
