<HEADLINE> Mozambique to Host Meeting of Indian Ocean Rim </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, April 9 (Xinhua) -- Mozambique has been designated to
host a meeting of the Council of Ministers of the Indian Ocean
Rim Association in 1999, which will prepare for a summit of heads
of state and government of its member states.
</P>
<P>
This was revealed today by Mozambican Foreign Minister
Leonardo Simao, who added that ports and airports of Maputo,
Beira and Nacala in Mozambique, which is a member of the newly
formed organization, will become pillars of trade between these
countries.
</P>
<P>
He further said member states of the organization established
in Mauritius on March 7 are enjoying good relationships.
</P>
<P>
Some other countries along the Indian Ocean have expressed
their wishes to join the organization. "A technical committee has
been set up to examine their applications," he said.
</P>
<P>
Cooperation among the member countries of the organization
will focus on trade and academic exchange, the minister
disclosed.
</P>
<P>
The Indian Ocean Rim Association comprises Australia, India,
Indonesia, Kenya, Madagascar, Malaysia, Mauritius, Mozambique,
Oman, Singapore, South Africa, Sri Lanka, Tanzania and Yemen.
</P>
</TEXT>
