<HEADLINE> Ugandan Rebels Kill Civilians Despite Non-violent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, April 9 (Xinhua) -- Lord's Resistance Army's (LRA)
rebels killed an unspecified number of civilians Tuesday despite
their non-violence commitment three days ago, local English
newspaper "The Monitor" reported today.
</P>
<P>
The atrocities occurred about 48 kilometers north of Northern
Gulu town, a witness told the paper. "By the time I left, the
number of dead civilians were not yet established," he said.
</P>
<P>
A local teacher said he heard heavy shellings yesterday from
the direction of the scene. But there was no official
confirmation.
</P>
<P>
The LRA rebels are Christian fundamentalists who have vowed to
topple President Y. Museveni.
</P>
<P>
The killings occurred just three days after James Obitas, the
LRA secretary for external relations and mass mobilization,
announced they would stop abducting civilians and other violences
against civilians.
</P>
<P>
In another development, Peter Odok Ochen, the new resident
district commissioner of Gulu, asked the government to absorb the
captured LRA members into the Ugandan army, according to local
English weekly "People" today.
</P>
<P>
The surrendered ones will join the government troops in
fighting against rebels and this would create an atmosphere of
confidence and belonging to the government side, the official
told Specicza Wandira Kazibwe, the inspecting vice-president.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
